docs.lead_paragraph: MINNEAPOLIS — Political leaders in Minnesota promised sweeping changes after George Floyd’s killing turned their state into a focal point for nationwide fury and grief over police killings and racism.

headline.main: Minnesota Lawmakers Vowed Police Reform. They Couldn’t Agree on Any.
headline.print_headline: Parties Point Fingers as Effort to Pass Police Reform Collapses in Minnesota

docs.abstract: The streaming service said it planned to eventually bring the 1939 film back “with a discussion of its historical context.”

docs.lead_paragraph: HBO Max has removed from its catalog “Gone With the Wind,” the 1939 movie long considered a triumph of American cinema but one that romanticizes the Civil War-era South while glossing over its racial sins.

headline.main: HBO Max Pulls ‘Gone With the Wind,’ Citing Racist Depictions

docs.abstract: Volunteers have provided first aid at protests since at least the 1960s. Many of them owe their training to Ann Hirschman.

docs.lead_paragraph: As protests against police brutality have swept the country, in some cases leading to additional police aggression, toward demonstrators, a loosely organized group of trained volunteers has been on call to intervene and treat injuries.

headline.print_headline: The Very Model of a Street-Healing Woman

docs.abstract: German officials were caught off guard after hundreds of young men attacked the police in Stuttgart, but others were less surprised, saying the clashes exposed long-simmering tensions with immigrants.
docs.snippet: German officials were caught off guard after hundreds of young men attacked the police in Stuttgart, but others were less surprised, saying the clashes exposed long-simmering tensions with immigrants.
docs.lead_paragraph: BERLIN — Ever since hundreds of young men attacked the police and vandalized dozens of stores in Germany on Saturday, the country has been wrestling with the question of why a routine check of a suspected drug dealer led to such an outpouring of violence.

headline.main: After Night of Violence Targeting Police, Germany Seeks ‘Roots of Anger’

docs.abstract: The encounter between a black man and the police on the Rockaway boardwalk came days after lawmakers made the use of chokeholds a criminal offense.
docs.snippet: The encounter between a black man and the police on the Rockaway boardwalk came days after lawmakers made the use of chokeholds a criminal offense.
docs.lead_paragraph: The New York Police Department on Sunday suspended a police officer who was involved in the arrest of a black man in Queens, after cellphone video of the encounter showed the officer appearing to use an illegal chokehold.

headline.main: After Video Shows Apparent Chokehold, N.Y.P.D. Suspends Officer

byline.original: By Ashley Southall and Mihir Zaveri

docs.abstract: From Virginia to New Mexico, protests over police brutality have brought hundreds of years of American history bubbling to the surface.
docs.snippet: From Virginia to New Mexico, protests over police brutality have brought hundreds of years of American history bubbling to the surface.
docs.lead_paragraph: The boiling anger that exploded in the days after George Floyd gasped his final breaths is now fueling a national movement to topple perceived symbols of racism and oppression in the United States, as protests over police brutality against African-Americans expand to include demands for a more honest accounting of American history.

headline.main: Reconsidering the Past, One Statue at a Time
headline.print_headline: Reconsidering the Past, One Statue at a Time

docs.lead_paragraph: Five days after George Floyd was killed while in custody of the Minneapolis police on May 25, N.F.L. Commissioner Roger Goodell released a 150-word statement about the death and ensuing protests. The N.H.L. and N.B.A. followed suit the next day.
